ProtoResult:
. "Suppose $n$ is the area of a right triangle with rational 
   side lengths $a, b, c$, with $a\leq b<c$. Let $A=(c/2)^2$. 
   Then $$A-n, A, and A+n$$ are all perfect squares of rational
   numbers."
